difficulty: If there was less information to comb through, versus more of the same. For example, the wine list had a huge amount of wines with names that were all incredibly similar. That made that incredibly difficult.
format: Whether it was easily confined to a column or row, versus cramming an entire paragraph into a box, which is awful to read and look through. Also, poor/sparse breaks between items.
comments: Fun task. I love hunting for information. No issues.
